$ %windir%\System32\inetsrv\config\ApplicationHost.config

`ApplicationHost.config` is the main (root) configuration file for IIS 7 and above. It defines
  • all sites
  • applications
  • virtual directories
  • application pools
  • global default settings (similar to the → Microsoft/dot-net → Windows/dirs/Windows/Microsoft_NET/Framework64/vn_n_n/Config/machine_config[`machine.config`] file)
